   "source": [
    "# 🔗 Covalent Docking Workflow using GNINA (Google Colab Compatible)\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook implements a robust covalent docking workflow using **GNINA**, an open-source molecular docking tool that supports deep learning scoring and covalent constraints. It is designed to be run in Google Colab.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Workflow Overview\n",
    "1. **Colab Environment Setup** — Install RDKit, download GNINA, and configure CUDA libraries.\n",
    "2. **Receptor Preparation** — Prepare the protein structure and identify the reactive residue.\n",
    "3. **Ligand Preparation** — Prepare the ligand and identify the warhead atom using SMILES input.\n",
    "4. **Covalent Docking** — Execute GNINA with covalent constraints.\n",
    "5. **Analysis** — Evaluate the docking poses and affinities."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1: Colab Environment Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "This cell sets up the Google Colab environment by installing necessary libraries and downloading the GNINA binary. **Run this cell first.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install RDKit (if not already installed in Colab)\n",
    "!pip install rdkit-pypi -q\n",
    "\n",
    "# Download GNINA v1.1 binary\n",
    "!wget https://github.com/gnina/gnina/releases/download/v1.1/gnina -O gnina\n",
    "!chmod +x gnina\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configure LD_LIBRARY_PATH for CUDA (Colab specific)\n",
    "import os\n",
    "# Find CUDA library path in Colab environment\n",
    "cuda_path = \"/usr/local/cuda/lib64\" # Common path in Colab\n",
    "if os.path.exists(cuda_path):\n",
    "    os.environ["LD_LIBRARY_PATH"] = f"{cuda_path}:" + os.environ.get("LD_LIBRARY_PATH", "")\n",
    "    print(f\"✅ LD_LIBRARY_PATH set to {os.environ["LD_LIBRARY_PATH"]}\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"⚠️ CUDA path not found at /usr/local/cuda/lib64. GNINA might fail if CUDA libraries are not in system path.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ Colab environment setup complete\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2: Receptor Preparation\n",
    "\n",
    "**Upload your `receptor_A.pdb` file to the Colab environment before running this cell.**\n",
    "\n",
    "Identify the reactive residue on the receptor. For SARS-CoV-2 Mpro, this is typically **Cys145**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "RECEPTOR_FILE = \"receptor_A.pdb\"\n",
    "REACTIVE_RESIDUE = \"A:145:SG\" # Chain:ResNum:AtomName (e.g., A:145:SG for Cys145)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"🎯 Target Residue: {REACTIVE_RESIDUE}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3: Ligand Preparation\n",
    "\n",
    "Provide the ligand as a SMILES string. The notebook will automatically generate a 3D conformer and identify the warhead atom using a SMARTS pattern. For a lactam warhead, we can use `C(=O)N`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from rdkit import Chem\n",
    "from rdkit.Chem import Draw, AllChem\n",
    "import os\n",
    "from IPython.display import display\n",
    "\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "#  USER INPUT — Provide your ligand SMILES here\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "LIGAND_SMILES = \"C1(=O)[C@H](C[C@@H](CCC(=O)OCC)NC(=O)[C@H](Cc2ccccc2)NC(=O)[C@@H](Cc2ccccc2)N)CCN1\" # Example: YVG ligand\n",
    "WARHEAD_SMARTS = \"C(=O)N\"\n",
    "LIGAND_FILE    = \"ligand_prepared.sdf\" # Output file for the prepared ligand\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "\n",
    "mol = None\n",
    "if LIGAND_SMILES:\n",
    "    print(f\"⚙️ Generating 3D conformer from SMILES: {LIGAND_SMILES}\")\n",
    "    mol = Chem.MolFromSmiles(LIGAND_SMILES)\n",
    "    if mol:\n",
    "        # Add hydrogens and generate 3D coordinates\n",
    "        mol = Chem.AddHs(mol)\n",
    "        AllChem.EmbedMolecule(mol, randomSeed=42)\n",
    "        AllChem.MMFFOptimizeMolecule(mol)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Save to SDF for GNINA\n",
    "        writer = Chem.SDWriter(LIGAND_FILE)\n",
    "        writer.write(mol)\n",
    "        writer.close()\n",
    "        print(f\"✅ Saved 3D ligand to {LIGAND_FILE}\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(\"❌ Invalid SMILES string. Please check your input.\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"❌ Please provide a valid SMILES string.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if mol:\n",
    "    pattern = Chem.MolFromSmarts(WARHEAD_SMARTS)\n",
    "    matches = mol.GetSubstructMatches(pattern)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if matches:\n",
    "        print(f\"✅ Warhead found at atom indices: {matches[0]}\")\n",
    "        # Visualize 2D structure with highlighted warhead\n",
    "        mol_2d = Chem.Mol(mol)\n",
    "        AllChem.Compute2DCoords(mol_2d)\n",
    "        display(Draw.MolToImage(mol_2d, highlightAtoms=matches[0]))\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(\"⚠️ Warhead pattern not found in the provided SMILES. Please check WARHEAD_SMARTS.\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"❌ Ligand molecule not successfully processed. Cannot identify warhead.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2: Receptor Preparation\n",
    "\n",
    "Identify the reactive residue on the receptor. For SARS-CoV-2 Mpro, this is typically **Cys145**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "RECEPTOR_FILE = \"receptor_A.pdb\"\n",
    "REACTIVE_RESIDUE = \"A:145:SG\" # Chain:ResNum:AtomName\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"🎯 Target Residue: {REACTIVE_RESIDUE}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3: Ligand Preparation\n",
    "\n",
    "Identify the warhead atom on the ligand using a SMARTS pattern. For a lactam warhead, we can use `C(=O)N`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from rdkit import Chem\n",
    "from rdkit.Chem import Draw, AllChem\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# Provide either a SMILES string or an SDF file path\n",
    "LIGAND_SMILES = \"C1(=O)[C@H](C[C@@H](CCC(=O)OCC)NC(=O)[C@H](Cc2ccccc2)NC(=O)[C@@H](Cc2ccccc2)N)CCN1\" # Example: YVG ligand\n",
    "LIGAND_FILE = \"ligand_prepared.sdf\"\n",
    "WARHEAD_SMARTS = \"C(=O)N\"\n",
    "\n",
    "if LIGAND_SMILES:\n",
    "    print(f\"⚙️ Generating 3D conformer from SMILES: {LIGAND_SMILES}\")\n",
    "    mol = Chem.MolFromSmiles(LIGAND_SMILES)\n",
    "    if mol:\n",
    "        mol = Chem.AddHs(mol)\n",
    "        AllChem.EmbedMolecule(mol, randomSeed=42)\n",
    "        AllChem.MMFFOptimizeMolecule(mol)\n",
    "        writer = Chem.SDWriter(LIGAND_FILE)\n",
    "        writer.write(mol)\n",
    "        writer.close()\n",
    "        print(f\"✅ Saved 3D ligand to {LIGAND_FILE}\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(\"❌ Invalid SMILES string\")\n",
    "elif os.path.exists(LIGAND_FILE):\n",
    "    print(f\"📥 Loading existing ligand from {LIGAND_FILE}\")\n",
    "    mol = Chem.MolFromMolFile(LIGAND_FILE, removeHs=False)\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"❌ Please provide a valid SMILES string or SDF file.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if mol:\n",
    "    pattern = Chem.MolFromSmarts(WARHEAD_SMARTS)\n",
    "    matches = mol.GetSubstructMatches(pattern)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if matches:\n",
    "        print(f\"✅ Warhead found at atom indices: {matches[0]}\")\n",
    "        # Visualize 2D structure with highlighted warhead\n",
    "        mol_2d = Chem.Mol(mol)\n",
    "        AllChem.Compute2DCoords(mol_2d)\n",
    "        display(Draw.MolToImage(mol_2d, highlightAtoms=matches[0]))\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(\"❌ Warhead pattern not found\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4: Covalent Docking\n",
    "\n",
    "Run GNINA with the `--covalent_rec_atom` and `--covalent_lig_atom_pattern` flags."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "CENTER = \"30.9291 -12.0193 7.00959\"\n",
    "SIZE = \"20 20 20\"\n",
    "OUTPUT_FILE = \"covalent_poses.sdf\"\n",
    "\n",
    "gnina_cmd = f\"./gnina --receptor {RECEPTOR_FILE} --ligand {LIGAND_FILE} --out {OUTPUT_FILE} \" \\\n",
    "            f\"--center_x 30.9291 --center_y -12.0193 --center_z 7.00959 \" \\\n",
    "            f\"--size_x 20 --size_y 20 --size_z 20 \" \\\n",
    "            f\"--covalent_rec_atom {REACTIVE_RESIDUE} \" \\\n",
    "            f\"--covalent_lig_atom_pattern '{WARHEAD_SMARTS}' \" \\\n",
    "            f\"--exhaustiveness 8 --cnn_scoring none\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Running: {gnina_cmd}\")\n",
    "!{gnina_cmd}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 5: Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Check the affinity of the generated poses."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "def get_affinities(sdf_file):\n",
    "    affinities = []\n",
    "    with open(sdf_file, 'r') as f:\n",
    "        lines = f.readlines()\n",
    "        for i, line in enumerate(lines):\n",
    "            if \"<minimizedAffinity>\" in line:\n",
    "                affinities.append(float(lines[i+1].strip()))\n",
    "    return affinities\n",
    "\n",
    "affs = get_affinities(OUTPUT_FILE)\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame(affs, columns=[\"Minimized Affinity\"])\n",
    "print(df)\n",
    "df.plot(kind='bar', title=\"Docking Affinities\")"
   ]
  }
